[Chronic Wasting Disease has been found many times in deer and elk in Colorado. This particular region, 77, represents a slight expansion of the disease.

Testing hunter-killed animals and road kill is part of the surveillance of many states. - Mod.TG

The state of Colorado can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at < https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4353091,209>.
Montrose County is located in southwest Colorado. A county map can be seen at http://geology.com/county-map/colorado-county-map.gif. - CopyEd.AO]
